   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         
            <opener rend="right">
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place">Department of the Interior,<lb/>
Washington, D. C.,</name>
                  <date when="1865-01-24">January 24, 1865.</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>Sir:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>You are hereby appointed to a Clerkship of the first class&#8212;in the Office of Indian Affairs, of this Department&#8212;the salary of which is $1200 per annum, to commence when you have subscribed the enclosed oath, and entered upon duty. I am, Sir, very respectfully, your obedient servant</p>  
            <closer rend="right">
               <signed>W. T. Otto, <lb/>Assistant Secretary.<ptr target="nyp.00220_n100"/>
            </signed>
            </closer>
         
         <postscript>
            <p>Walt Whitman, Esq.<lb/>
of New York</p>
         </postscript>
      </body>
